8 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
9 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
10 the following form:
11 BALLOT TITLE
12 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
13 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
14 This measure amends Section 8B and Section 8C of Article 10 of
15 the Oklahoma Constitution. Section 8B currently limits annual
16 growth in fair cash value of most types of real property to five
17 percent (5%) or to three percent (3%) for homesteads. For real
18 property for which a homestead exemption is granted and real
19 property classified as agricultural land, it would limit growth
20 to one and seventy-five-hundredths percent (1.75%) for 2027 and
21 subsequent years. For other types of real property, it would
22 limit growth in fair cash value to four percent (4%) annually.
23 The measure would change Section 8C in Article 10 that prohibits
24 any increase in fair cash value of homestead property for
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR S. J. R. NO. 39 Page 7

1 persons age sixty-five (65) or older whose income does not
2 exceed certain limits. This provision is sometimes referred to
3 as the “senior freeze”. Instead of prohibiting any increase in
4 fair cash value for these homesteads, there would be an annual
5 limit of one and seventy-five-hundredths percent (1.75%). The
6 income test for this new structure would be different. The
7 annual limit could be reduced based on how much gross household
8 income the homestead owner had in the preceding year. Depending
9 on the amount of gross household income the property owner had
10 in the preceding year, if the income level was one hundred
11 percent (100%) or less of the income amount determined using an
12 income measurement from federal law, the fair cash value of the
13 homestead could not increase. If the income amount was in
14 excess of certain thresholds, the limit on increases in fair
15 cash value for homesteads owned by persons age sixty-five (65)
16 or older could be thirty-five-hundredths percent (0.35%), seven-
17 tenths percent (0.7%), one and five-hundredths percent (1.05%),
18 one and four-tenths percent (1.4%) or one and seventy-five-
19 hundredths percent (1.75%).
20 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
21 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
22 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
23 SECTION 3. A special election is hereby ordered to be held
24 throughout the State of Oklahoma on the date of August 25, 2026, at
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR S. J. R. NO. 39 Page 8

1 whic h time the proposed amendment to the Oklahoma Constitution, as
2 set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution, shall be submitted to the
3 people of Oklahoma for their approval or rejection as and in the
4 manner provided by law.
5 SECTION 4. The President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall,
6 immediately after the passage of this resolution, prepare and file
7 one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in SECTION 2
8 hereof, with the Secretary of State and one copy with the Attorney
9 General."
